<T>(
  nestedObject: NestedObject<T>,
  isLeaf?: (content: NestedObject<T> | T | undefined) => boolean
) => {
  Object.keys(nestedObject).map((key) => {
    const value = nestedObject[key];

    const isValueLeaf = isLeaf ? isLeaf(value) : typeof value !== "object";

    return;
  });
}
name: flattenNestedObject
description:
Flattens a nested object by returning an object that hasa the nested path as the key and the leaf as the value
